The relentless stress students experience could be the cause of concentration lapse as their focus is constantly imposed to stay on the academic work. The unacademic subjects on the syllabus such as cookery could be a pressure relief and reduce students’ focus as it teaches the importance of nutrition and health. Social works could help students’ who follow certain majors that involve communication. It also benefits people’s health, subjects such as physical education is essential to maintain their health during tough studies. Changing the centralization of a focus stimulates students to increase their study quality.
